Breaking news (Photo: The Republic)

A man was arrested on suspicion of running over another man with a vehicle, causing serious injuries, during a fight on Thursday night in Chandler, according to police.

Police were called to the area near Chandler Boulevard and Federal Street, just west of the Loop 101, in response to a fight.

One man allegedly ran over the other, resulting in serious injuries, according to Chandler police spokesman Seth Tyler. One suspect was arrested.

The victim is in stable condition, and the investigation is ongoing, police said.

